cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with object detection in videos using deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of regularization and optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper uses video datasets, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning models for object detection, which is a common application of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well.
